# UDS Design Language

This rule documents the **standard visual constructions** that UDS uses for
states (Default / Hover / Active / Focus / Filled / Selected / Error /
Disabled / Read-only / Loading), surface treatments, elevation, border
radius, density, and selection.

The standards here are **derived from the existing component CSS** under
`uds-docs/uds/components/*/<id>.css`. Where components disagree, both
patterns are documented and the disagreement is listed in the "Known
inconsistencies" section at the bottom for designer review.

This is the partner to:

- [`uds-token-architecture.mdc`](./uds-token-architecture.mdc) — what
  tokens exist (vocabulary).
- [`uds-figma-factory-quality.mdc`](./uds-figma-factory-quality.mdc) —
  process for how factory builds use them.
- [`uds-figma-plugin-api-gotchas.mdc`](./uds-figma-plugin-api-gotchas.mdc)
  — Plugin API specifics for `use_figma` work.

This rule is the **how things look** layer. Tokens are the *what's
available*, factory-quality is the *how to apply them mechanically*,
this is the *what they should resolve to visually per state*.

---

## 1. Interaction states

### 1.1 Default (rest)

The neutral, non-interactive look. No pseudo-classes, no `[data-state]`,
no `[aria-*]` attributes.

| Element family | Background | Border | Text |
|---|---|---|---|
| Form field (text-input, dropdown, text-area, search) | `surface-main` | `border-primary` 1 px INSIDE | `text-primary` (value) / `text-secondary` (placeholder) |
| Form control (checkbox, radio) | transparent inner | `border-primary` 1–2 px | `text-primary` (label) |
| Button — primary | `surface-interactive-default` | `surface-interactive-default` 1 px | `text-inverse` |
| Button — secondary | `surface-interactive-none` | `border-interactive` 1 px | `text-brand` |
| Button — ghost | `surface-interactive-none` | transparent | `text-brand` |
| Tile / card | `surface-main` | `border-primary` 1 px | `text-primary` |
| Chip | `surface-interactive-none` | `border-primary` 1 px | `text-primary` |
| Link | n/a (text) | n/a | `text-interactive`, underlined |
| Tab | transparent | 2 px bottom transparent | `text-primary` |

### 1.2 Hover

Pointer is over the element, not yet committed.

| Family | Treatment | Token(s) |
|---|---|---|
| Form field (text-input ↔ inconsistent, see §11) | — | (text-input has no hover today; dropdown/search use `surface-interactive-subtle-hover` background + `border-interactive`) |
| Form field — dropdown trigger | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-hover`, border → `border-interactive` | dropdown.css |
| Form field — search field | bg → `surface-subtle` | search.css |
| Form field — text-area | border → `border-outline-hover` | text-area.css |
| Form control (checkbox, radio) | border → `border-interactive` | checkbox.css, radio.css |
| Button — primary | bg → `surface-interactive-hover`, border → matching | button.css |
| Button — secondary / ghost | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-hover` (the `_btn-subtle-hover` var) | button.css |
| Tile | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle` | tile.css |
| Chip | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-hover` | chip.css |
| Tab (non-selected) | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-hover`, text → `text-interactive` | tabs.css |
| Tab (selected) | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-hover`, bottom-border → `border-interactive-hover` | tabs.css |
| Link | text → `text-interactive-hover` | link.css |
| Dropdown menu item | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-hover` | dropdown.css |
| Trailing icon button inside a field | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-hover` | text-input.css, dropdown.css, search.css |

**Standard hover for new form fields:** match dropdown's pattern —
`bg → surface-interactive-subtle-hover, border → border-interactive`.
This is the most explicit "this is interactive" signal in the system.

### 1.3 Active / Pressed

Mouse-down state. Short-lived; transitions back to Hover on mouse-up.

| Family | Treatment | Token(s) |
|---|---|---|
| Button — primary | bg → `surface-interactive-active` | button.css |
| Button — secondary / ghost | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-active` | button.css |
| Form field — dropdown trigger (also `data-open="true"`) | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-active`, border → `border-interactive` | dropdown.css |
| Chip | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-active` | chip.css |
| Dropdown menu item | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-active` | dropdown.css |
| Link | text → `text-interactive-active` (also used for `aria-current="page"`) | link.css |

### 1.4 Focus (keyboard-only)

**This is the most important state to get right** because it has three
distinct constructions in the system and each has theme-safety
implications. See §6 below for the focus-ring deep dive.

Use `:focus-visible`, not `:focus` — the latter triggers on every click
and produces visual noise. `:focus-visible` only fires for keyboard
focus.

