## 2. Validation states

### 2.1 Error

Recolors the relevant chrome to error red and bolds the label/value.

| Element | Treatment |
|---|---|
| Field border (form field) | `border-error` 1 px |
| Field text (text-input value when in error) | `text-error` |
| Placeholder when in error | `text-error` |
| Label | color → `text-error`, weight → `bold` |
| Helper text | color → `text-error` |
| Counter inside helper row | stays `text-secondary` (NOT recolored — text-input.css line 233) |
| Leading icon | color → `icon-error` |
| Required dot | already `icon-error`, stays |
| Form control inner box (checkbox) | bg → `surface-interactive-red-subtle`, border → `border-error` |
| Form control outer ring (radio) | border → `border-error` |
| Radio dot when selected + error | bg → `icon-error` |
| Label of a form control with error | color → `text-error`, weight → `bold` |
| Focus ring on a field in error | stays blue (`outline-focus-visible`) — NOT recolored to red; matches text-input.css line 211 |
| Focus ring on a search field in error | recolored to `border-error` — search.css deviates from text-input |

### 2.2 Success / Warning / Info

Used by `notification` and `badge`. Not used as a *state* of an
interactive element today. Pattern:

| Variant | Subtle background | Subtle text | Prominent background | Prominent text |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Info | `surface-info-subtle` | `text-info` | `surface-info` | `text-inverse` |
| Success | `surface-success-subtle` | `text-success` | `surface-success` | `text-inverse` |
| Error | `surface-error-subtle` | `text-error` | `surface-error` | `text-inverse` |
| Warning | `surface-warning-subtle` | `text-warning` | `surface-warning` | `text-inverse` |

Icon family: `icon-{variant}` matches the text family.

