## 3. Availability states

### 3.1 Disabled

Non-interactive. Pointer events blocked, cursor `not-allowed`.

UDS has **three distinct disabled patterns** depending on the element
family:

| Pattern | When used | Treatment |
|---|---|---|
| **Filled-disabled** | Buttons (primary, secondary), form fields with a background | bg → `surface-interactive-disabled`, border → transparent OR `border-disabled` (inconsistent — see §11), text → `text-disabled-bold` |
| **Outlined-disabled** | Form controls (checkbox, radio) | border → `border-disabled`, no bg change, label → `text-disabled` |
| **Text-only-disabled** | Ghost button, link, tab, toggle label | text → `text-disabled`, `pointer-events: none`, `cursor: not-allowed` |
| **Reduced-opacity-disabled** | Toggle | border → `border-disabled`, `opacity: 0.7` (the only place opacity is used for state — see §11) |

Disabled text uses `text-disabled` for general copy and
`text-disabled-bold` for the *value* of a form field (where the user's
input was the entered text — needs slightly higher contrast to remain
legible).

### 3.2 Read-only

Looks like a field but accepts no edits. Implemented inconsistently
today (currently only partially supported in code; the Text Input
draft in Figma is the first explicit treatment).

**Recommended treatment (proposed):**
- Background → `surface-subtle` (tinted surface, theme-adaptive)
- Border → `border-primary` 1 px (same as Default, keeps the field
  shape legible)
- Text → `text-primary` (full opacity, user can read the value)
- No focus / hover rings on a read-only field
- `<input readonly>` attribute on the underlying input

Distinct from Disabled by:
- Read-only keeps text at full primary color (you can read the value);
  Disabled greys it.
- Read-only keeps the visible border; Disabled drops it for the filled
  treatment.
- Read-only still allows text selection and copy; Disabled blocks all
  interaction.

### 3.3 Loading

Not specified in UDS today. Components that need loading currently use
Disabled as the closest approximation (see text-input.css known issues
in `spec.json`). Deferred &mdash; waiting on designer review.

