## 7. Surface treatments

UDS distinguishes between **page surfaces** (the background canvas),
**content surfaces** (cards, panels, modals), and **interactive
surfaces** (anything that responds to pointer or keyboard).

### 7.1 Page surfaces

| Token | Usage |
|---|---|
| `--uds-color-surface-page-main` | The page background. Light: neutral-10. Dark: neutral-110. |
| `--uds-color-surface-page-subtle` | A secondary page area (sidebar background, etc.). |
| `--uds-color-surface-page-alt` | An alternate page area. |
| `--uds-color-surface-page-bold` | A bolder page area (e.g. dark header on light page). |

### 7.2 Content surfaces

| Token | Usage |
|---|---|
| `--uds-color-surface-main` | The default surface for any contained content. Cards, panels, fields, tiles, tooltips. |
| `--uds-color-surface-subtle` | A subtle tint on top of `surface-main`. Used for: dialog header, search hover, tile hover (via `surface-interactive-subtle`), read-only fields. |
| `--uds-color-surface-alt` | An alternate surface tint. |
| `--uds-color-surface-bold` / `-xbold` / `-xxbold` | Progressively bolder surfaces. |
| `--uds-color-surface-inverse` | The contrast-surface (used by `text-inverse`-on-it). |
| `--uds-color-surface-white` | LITERAL WHITE in every theme. Use sparingly — almost never the right token. Often confused with `surface-main`. |
| `--uds-color-surface-black` | LITERAL BLACK in every theme. Same caveat. |

### 7.3 Interactive surfaces

| Token | Usage |
|---|---|
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-none` | Transparent / nothing. Default for ghost buttons, dropdown items at rest. |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-neutral` | A neutral interactive bg (dropdown trigger uses this). |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-default` | The brand-saturated interactive color. Primary buttons, checkbox checked, toggle checked. |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-hover` | Hover state of `interactive-default`. |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-active` | Pressed state of `interactive-default`. Chip selected. |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-disabled` | Disabled bg. Filled form fields, primary buttons. |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-subtle` | A faint tint of the interactive color. Tile hover. |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-subtle-hover` | Hover of `interactive-subtle`. Used by: secondary buttons, ghost buttons, chip, tab, dropdown item, search hover. |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-subtle-active` | Pressed of `interactive-subtle`. Same family as above. |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-red-*` | Destructive variants. Used by `[data-btn-color="danger"]` buttons and error treatments. |

### 7.4 Status surfaces

| Token | Usage |
|---|---|
| `--uds-color-surface-info` / `-subtle` | Info notifications and badges. |
| `--uds-color-surface-success` / `-subtle` | Success notifications and badges. |
| `--uds-color-surface-error` / `-subtle` | Error notifications, badges, and checkbox error inner box. |
| `--uds-color-surface-warning` / `-subtle` | Warning notifications and badges. |

