## 8. Elevation / shadow scale

```
toggle thumb        → --uds-shadow-depth-100   (lifted control)
tooltip             → --uds-shadow-depth-300   (transient popover)
dropdown menu       → --uds-shadow-depth-300   (transient popover)
dialog              → --uds-shadow-depth-500   (modal / page-level)
```

| Token | Resolved (light theme) | Use when… |
|---|---|---|
| `--uds-shadow-depth-100` | `0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1)` | A small element is *lifted* off its surface. Toggle thumb. |
| `--uds-shadow-depth-300` | `0 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08)` | A transient overlay near its trigger. Tooltips, dropdowns, popovers, menus. |
| `--uds-shadow-depth-500` | `0 10px 20px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2)` | A modal that floats above the entire page. Dialogs, sheets. |
| `--uds-shadow-bento` | `0 6px 16px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.16)` | Bento-style card grouping (specific to dashboard layouts). |

Backdrop overlay (under modals): `--uds-overlay-backdrop` (`rgba(0,0,0,0.45)`).

Do NOT bind elevation tokens to non-elevation effects. The shadow scale
exists to communicate depth, not decoration.

