## 9. Border radius scale

| Token | Used for | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| `--uds-border-radius-input` | Form fields, buttons, list items, anything you can interact with that's not a chip | text-input field, dropdown trigger, button, dialog close button, tile |
| `--uds-border-radius-input-full` | Fully-rounded form / button | (defined; not yet used in components I sampled) |
| `--uds-border-radius-input-selected` | When a form item is selected (slightly larger radius to read as chunkier) | (defined; usage TBD) |
| `--uds-border-radius-container-sm` | Small surfaces, focus halos on inline elements | notification, badge, link focus, tab focus |
| `--uds-border-radius-container` | Medium surfaces, tooltips | tooltip, chip |
| `--uds-border-radius-container-md` | Medium content cards | (defined; usage TBD) |
| `--uds-border-radius-container-lg` | Larger content cards | (defined; usage TBD) |
| `--uds-border-radius-container-xl` | Largest content cards | dialog (24 px) |
| `--uds-border-radius-container-full` | Pills, circular elements | toggle control, toggle thumb |

Pattern: form/button family uses `input`. Surface family uses
`container-*` with the suffix indicating relative size.

