## 10. Density / sizing patterns

UDS supports two density tracks:

| Track | Selector | Notable changes vs. default |
|---|---|---|
| Default (comfortable) | (none) | Full padding, base font size |
| Small (`sm`) | `data-size="sm"` | Tighter vertical padding, same font size |

### Per-component sm-vs-default deltas

| Component | Default | Small |
|---|---|---|
| Button | `padding: var(--uds-space-150) var(--uds-space-200)` (12 × 16 px) | `padding: var(--uds-space-075) var(--uds-space-150)` (6 × 12 px) |
| Tab | `padding: var(--uds-space-200) var(--uds-space-300)` (16 × 24 px) | `padding-top/bottom: var(--uds-space-100)` (8 px) |
| Text input (proposed, Figma factory draft) | min-height 48 px, padding 6 px / 8 px, font `font-size-base` | min-height 36 px, padding 4 px / 6 px, font `font-size-sm` |
| Badge | full padding, font-size-base | `padding: var(--uds-space-025) var(--uds-space-050)`, `font-size-xs` |

There is no `lg` size in UDS today. New components that need a bigger
size should check with the designer before adding one.

