## 12. Known inconsistencies (for designer review)

These are real disagreements between components in the current CSS.
They are listed here so the designer can pick a standard pattern. Until
they do, factory builds default to whichever option is the safest across
themes and document the choice.

### 12.1 Focus ring gap binding

| Component | Gap binding | Theme-safe? |
|---|---|---|
| button | `surface-white` | ✗ (white in dark mode) |
| text-input | `surface-white` | ✗ |
| dropdown trigger | `surface-white` | ✗ |
| chip | `surface-main` | ✓ |
| search | `surface-main` | ✓ |

**Suggested fix**: bind the gap to `surface-main` everywhere. Three
components need
updating to match. Cannot autonomously edit per
[`uds-source-of-truth.mdc`](./uds-source-of-truth.mdc) — flag it as a
sync gap for the next Figma → code round trip.

### 12.2 Hover treatment for form fields

| Component | Hover treatment |
|---|---|
| text-input | (no hover state defined) |
| dropdown trigger | bg → `surface-interactive-subtle-hover`, border → `border-interactive` |
| search field | bg → `surface-subtle` (no border change) |
| text-area | border → `border-outline-hover` (no bg change) |

**Suggested fix**: use text-area's `border-outline-hover` everywhere.
It reads as hover without competing visually with the focus ring.
Designer review.

### 12.3 Disabled border treatment

| Component | Disabled border |
|---|---|
| button (primary) | `surface-interactive-disabled` (same as bg — invisible border) |
| button (secondary) | `transparent` |
| text-input | `transparent` |
| dropdown trigger | `border-disabled` |
| checkbox | `border-disabled` |
| radio | `border-disabled` |
| tile | `border-disabled` |

**Suggested fix**: use `border-disabled` on outlined elements (form
controls) and `transparent` on filled elements (filled disabled
buttons, text-input filled disabled style). Both treatments are
fine — they communicate slightly different things about disabled.

### 12.4 Toggle's opacity for disabled

Toggle uses `opacity: 0.7` for disabled. No other component does this.
Either toggle is the only correct one and others should follow, or
toggle is the outlier and should drop the opacity. Designer review.

### 12.5 Required dot color

| Component | Required dot color |
|---|---|
| text-input | `icon-error` (red) |
| dropdown | `icon-error` (red) |
| checkbox | `icon-error` (red) |
| radio | `icon-error` (red) |
| tile | `text-error` (red) — different token, same family |

Trivially inconsistent — text-error and icon-error resolve to the same
red. Pick one and use it everywhere.

